<dl id="n40080b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40080b">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40080b"> 80(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> sotadic belt</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Subsequent enquiries in many and distant countries enabled me to arrive at the following conclusions: &mdash; 1. There exists what I call a &ldquo;Sotadic Zone&rdquo; &hellip; <small> Richard F. Burton, &ldquo;Terminal Essay&rdquo;, <a name="RBTE2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RBTE2"><cite title="source">The Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night</cite></a> (n.d.) X, 206</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Burton proceeds to draw its geographic boundaries, and refers to it in subsequent lines as a belt. Unit repeated at <a name="n56127h" href="n56all.htm#n56127h">N56 (VI.B.41):127(h)</a>. </mm> </dd></dl>
